cs.CR, cs.SD, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.CY 

The paper discusses a privacy issue related to computer keyboards and presents a new keyboard acoustic eavesdropping attack that involves Voice-over-IP (VoIP). This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of Computer Security (cs.CR), Sound and Music Computing (cs.SD), Multimedia (cs.MM), Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), or Computers and Society (cs.CY). However, since the paper primarily focuses on the security aspect of the attack, cs.CR is the most likely category. The other categories are also possible because the paper involves sound and multimedia processing, human-computer interaction, and societal implications of the attack.
